article.headline: Hawaii 97, Texas Southern 67
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Phil Martin scored 18 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead four players into double figures as Hawaii defeated Texas Southern 97-67 Friday night in the opening round of the round-robin Adidas Festival. Bobby Nash scored 13 points off the bench and Jason Carter and Julian Sensley each added 10 apiece for Hawaii (4-2). Damien Smith led the Tigers (3-5) with a game-high 27 points. Hawaii took control of the game with a 28-11 run in the final 11 minutes of the first half. The Rainbow Warriors hit four 3-pointers during the stretch, including two by Jake Sottos, to lead 51-33 at halftime. Prior to the run, Texas Southern led briefly twice, 2-0 and 5-2. Trailing 20-9, the Tigers used an 11-6 run to cut the deficit to six points before Hawaii went on the long run. Texas Southern had no answer to the UH offense that shot 52 percent (36-of-68) from the field and led by as many as 30 points in the second half. The Tigers shot 41 percent (25-of-60) but turned the ball over 22 times.
